Canadian Charity Bylaws Template
AlphaProMega Air Foundation
Bylaws
Adopted: [Insert Date – e.g. February 15, 2026]
Article 1 – Name & Purpose
1.1 The name of the corporation is AlphaProMega Air Foundation (the “Foundation”).
1.2 The Foundation is incorporated under the Canada Not-for-profit Corporations Act (CNCA).
1.3 The purposes of the Foundation are exclusively charitable and include:
a. The advancement of education through the development and free dissemination of open-source knowledge, tools, frameworks, and resources in artificial general intelligence, zero-emission technologies, sustainable systems, and ethical technological progress.
b. The advancement of science and research for public benefit by conducting and supporting non-profit inquiry into safe AGI architectures, post-scarcity energy systems, biomimetic engineering, biosignature detection protocols for celestial bodies, and self-replicating robotic systems for sustainable space resource utilization.
c. Any other exclusively charitable purposes recognized by the Canada Revenue Agency.
Article 2 – Head Office
2.1 The head office of the Foundation shall be situated at 73 Kingmount Crescent, Richmond Hill, Ontario L4B 3X4, or such other place in Canada as the directors may from time to time determine.
Article 3 – Directors
3.1 The affairs of the Foundation shall be managed by a board of directors (the “Board”).
3.2 Number of directors: Minimum 1, maximum 13 (as determined by the directors).
3.3 Initial director: Sherif Botros.
3.4 Directors serve until resignation, removal, or death.
3.5 Directors must act honestly, in good faith, and in the best interests of the Foundation.
3.6 No remuneration for directors except reimbursement of reasonable expenses.
3.7 No director shall receive any profit or gain from their position.
3.8 Conflicts of interest must be disclosed; conflicted directors abstain from voting.
Article 4 – Meetings of Directors
4.1 Meetings may be held in person, by telephone, video conference, or other electronic means.
4.2 Quorum: Majority of directors (or 1 if sole director).
4.3 Notice: Not required if all directors waive notice.
4.4 Resolutions: Majority vote; sole director may pass resolutions in writing.
4.5 Annual meeting: Within 15 months of last annual meeting (may be held virtually).
Article 5 – Officers
5.1 The Board may appoint officers (President, Secretary, Treasurer, etc.).
5.2 Initial officers: Sherif Botros (President & Secretary).
5.3 Officers serve at the pleasure of the Board.
5.4 Duties: President chairs meetings; Secretary keeps minutes; Treasurer manages finances.
Article 6 – Members
6.1 The Foundation has no members (non-membership corporation).
6.2 All powers rest with the directors.
Article 7 – Financial Matters
7.1 Fiscal year: January 1 – December 31.
7.2 Banking: Accounts at a Canadian financial institution.
7.3 Signing officers: Any two directors, or sole director if applicable.
7.4 No dividends or profit distribution to directors or members.
7.5 All funds used exclusively for charitable purposes.
Article 8 – Books & Records
8.1 The Foundation shall keep proper books of account, minutes of meetings, and records of all activities.
8.2 Records available for inspection by directors and CRA upon request.
Article 9 – Amendments
9.1 Bylaws may be amended by special resolution of the directors (2/3 vote).
9.2 Amendments must maintain exclusively charitable status and be filed with Corporations Canada if required.
Article 10 – Dissolution
10.1 Upon dissolution, remaining assets shall be distributed to one or more qualified donees (registered charities) with similar purposes, as determined by the directors.
Article 11 – Execution of Documents
11.1 Contracts, deeds, etc. may be signed by any director or officer authorized by resolution.
Adoption
These bylaws were adopted by resolution of the director(s) on [Insert Date].
Signed:
Sherif Botros, Director
